textAfterTable: 90482 Orcus I           Discovered 2005 Nov. 13 by T.-A. Suer and M. E. Brown at Palomar. Vanth is a daimon in Etruscan mythology who guides the dead to the underworld. She often appears on tomb paintings and sarcophagi, where she is depicted with wings and a torch. She is frequently shown in the presence of Charun, a guard of the underworld. The name was suggested by S. Taaffe.
